      "title": "Checkpoint Age (time since last success)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "description": "Rate of handler-phase event-flush triggers, by trigger type. `time` fires on the flusher interval; `size` fires when the queue hits the size threshold; `shutdown` fires from Phase 5b of GracefulShutdown. Under sustained load `size` should dominate `time`.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "spanNulls": false },
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 67 },
      "id": 58,
      "options": {
        "legend": { "calcs": ["mean"], "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom" },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(ledger_event_flush_triggers_total[5m])) by (trigger, region)",
          "legendFormat": "{{trigger}} / {{region}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Event Flush Rate (by trigger)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "description": "p50 and p99 of a single handler-phase event flush (drain + commit_in_memory into events.db page cache). Durability of flushed entries is realised on the next StateCheckpointer tick.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "spanNulls": false },
          "unit": "s"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 67 },
      "id": 59,
      "options": {
        "legend": { "calcs": ["mean", "max"], "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom" },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum(rate(ledger_event_flush_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])) by (le, region))",
          "legendFormat": "p50 {{region}}",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum(rate(ledger_event_flush_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])) by (le, region))",
          "legendFormat": "p99 {{region}}",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Event Flush Duration",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "description": "Queue depth sampled at flush entry — per-region snapshot of how full the bounded FlushQueue is when the flusher starts draining. A sustained high value indicates producers outrunning the flusher; tune `flush_interval_ms` or `queue_capacity`.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "spanNulls": false },
          "unit": "short"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 75 },
      "id": 60,
      "options": {
        "legend": { "calcs": ["mean", "max"], "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom" },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "ledger_event_flush_queue_depth",
          "legendFormat": "depth / {{region}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Event Flush Queue Depth",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "description": "Event overflows (dropped handler-phase events) by cause, plus flush failures. `queue_full` means producers outran the flusher; `shutdown_timeout` means Phase 5b drain didn't complete; `channel_closed` is a programming bug. Any non-zero sustained rate is alertable — events are best-effort but drops should be rare.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "spanNulls": false },
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 75 },
      "id": 61,
      "options": {
        "legend": { "calcs": ["mean", "max"], "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom" },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
